NAME
    @ / ai - send a prompt to the AI assistant

SYNOPSIS
    @ <prompt>
    ai <prompt>
    <input> | @ [prompt]
    <input> | ai [prompt]

DESCRIPTION
    Send a prompt to the AI assistant and receive a streaming response.
    The AI has context about your current session including working
    directory and username.

    When data is piped to the command, it is included as input context
    for the AI to analyze or transform.

OPTIONS
    None. All arguments are treated as the prompt.

ENVIRONMENT
    ANTHROPIC_API_KEY
        Required. Your Anthropic API key for authentication.

EXAMPLES
    Ask a question:
        @ what is the capital of France?

    Analyze piped data:
        cat /api/data/users | @ summarize this data

    Transform data:
        select * from users | @ convert to csv format

    Query with context:
        cat error.log | @ what went wrong?

    Chain with other commands:
        @ list 10 random words | sort

EXIT STATUS
    0   Success
    1   Error (missing API key, API error, no prompt)
    130 Interrupted (SIGINT)

SEE ALSO
    echo(1), cat(1), select(1)
